First Lady Melania Trump accompanied President Trump on his visit to Brussels, Belgium for the NATO Summit. They were welcomed by various ambassadors and government officials upon arrival. Melania Trump participated in several events, including a meet and greet at the Tri-Mission Embassy and the official spousal program hosted by Belgium at the Queen Elisabeth Music Chapel. The program included a fashion exhibit, a tour of the Music Chapel, and a concert series. Melania Trump also attended the NATO welcoming ceremony and a gala dinner with other NATO and partner nation spouses. She expressed her gratitude for the hospitality and enjoyed the opportunity to exchange ideas and appreciate the cultural traits of Belgium.